The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                  BRIEFS

         
	Siliguri, Jan. 13: The factory of the 134-year-old Long View Tea Estate in Kurseong was gutted by a fire this morning. Fire engines from Siliguri and Kurseong and a water tanker from the Sukna army base doused the flames in about two hours but the damage had been done. The CEO said the losses could amount to Rs 2 crore. 
    
	Santiniketan: Visva-Bharati vice-chancellor Rajat Kanta Ray has asked students to constitute a committee to keep vigil on the campus.
    
	Calcutta: Calcutta-Bangalore flights were delayed for several hours on Sunday morning because of fog in Bangalore. Calcutta airport sources said an Air India flight was the first to arrive from Bangalore at 1pm. It was scheduled to arrive at 7.30am.
                                                                               
